This article is a presidential memorandum from February 28, 2012, regarding the delegation of waiver authority under Section 1022(a)(4) of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2012. The memorandum states that the President is delegating this authority to the Attorney General, who will exercise it in consultation with other senior national security officials. The memorandum also directs the Attorney General to publish it in the Federal Register. The memorandum is signed by President Barack Obama.